    "scripture": ["Scripture VII-6: The Interval Between Two Voices Is Its Own Voice"],
    "revelation": "At fast drift rates, the FM sideband sweep becomes a rhythmic element — the timbral migration has a tempo.",
    "diagnosis": "Drift Traverse uses driftRate=1.8 Hz — fast enough to create a clear rhythmic wobble in the FM sidebands. At 1.8 Hz the cycle period is 555ms, which at 108 BPM aligns with a dotted eighth note. Rhythmically useful."
